timeline.bodyText:
I do not have the knowledge of design. But you are forwarding a complex structure Listener to gRPC, which seems very unnecessary. You could make the converted data as flat as possible. That's another reason to use converted data instead of proto.
From existing code I see, I think at least the layer of this Listener encapsulation is redundant.
class ListenerUpdate {
  private String listenerName;
  private String listeningAddr;
  private List<FilterChain> filterChains;
}
I don't know whether FilterChain can be further flattened or not depending on your design.

